ight, I got a 63 rogue, but decided I wanted to make a warrior.  He's level 13 now, only played him for a day, but need some weapon suggestions.  I hope to get a decent amount of plat soon.  Atm he has a Lamentation and a Jagged Blade of Mourning.  First of all, of these two, which should be primary? Then also, whats a good weapon I could upgrade these from?  Thanks for the input.<br>
<br>
-Dark- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xiththewizard>Xith the Wizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/03 2:54:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5012.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Warrior, need some opinions on weapons.</span><hr size=1> Lammy Main hand ... the quicker weapon in main hand always, damage bonus doesnt affect offhand, and the best ratio (unless its your quickest weapon) in offhand, so as to maximize your offhand damage.<br>
<br>
Ultimatly you want procs, aggro procs.<br>
<br>
Damage does not equal aggro procs.  Debuffs, stuns, Dots, tash ect are things you want to hold aggro.<br>
<br>
First off, i would ditch the Jagged Blade of mourning for a frostbringer.  Frosty wont proc for you yet, but the ratio is still superior, starts procing in the 30s if i remember correctly.  It procs a 60dd -15ac debuff.  It will be your main aggro weapon for a long long time.<br>
<br>
If you can afford it, spring for a wavecrasher for mainhand (these can be a little pricy, but its one of the top buyable aggro weapons in the game ... note BUYABLE).  Slow/Dot proc, simillar to Willsapper and Trident of the Deep sea, though not as effective, still uses the same kind of aggro.<br>
<br>
If your on a tight budget, you could always go for a JStick (journeymans walking stick), with a delay of 24, its not bad for low levels, and if youve ever seen what happens to a chanter when they chain tash, youll understand its effectiveness, JStick procs a tash.<br>
<br>
BBOT (Black Blade of Tormenting) supposedly draws decent aggro (ive never used one, so only know what ive been told), but youd probably be better off with your JBoM, due to the superior ratio, and higher damage component of the JBoM.<br>
<br>
But effectivly, aim for a frostbringer as your first weapon purchase to replace the JBoM, then save for wavecrasher for mainhand (same ratio as Lammy, Mainhand only, but the proc is worth every penny).<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp, hope it helps .... though im sure most of us here are of a like mind about what to go for as far as weapons.<br>
<br>
oh ... if you have more cash than you need, you could always buy a SoD ... but whats the chances of that. <p>Master Xith N'Shezbenon<br>
